-- Newcastle Beats Wigan 3-0 as Ba’s Two Goals Snap Run of Losses
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2012-12-03T22:12:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-03/newcastle-beats-wigan-3-0-as-ba-s-two-goals-snap-run-of-losses.html
Demba Ba scored twice to push
Newcastle to a 3-0 victory over Wigan, ending a run of four
straight Premier League defeats for the soccer team.  Ba scored a penalty in the 13th minute after Wigan was
reduced to 10 men when defender Maynor Figueroa brought down
Papiss Cisse in the box. Ba scored again eight minutes later,
and then Gael Bigirimana finished the scoring in the 71st
minute.  The win keeps Newcastle in 14th place, but it’s tied on 17
points with Fulham, which has a better goal difference. Wigan in
in 15th.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  